\
Satan\'92s False Light Patterns in the NT:\
	1.	False Teachers: Claiming divine authority while twisting Scripture (2 Peter 2:1).\
	2.	Counterfeit Miracles: Deceiving with signs and wonders (2 Thess. 2:9).\
	3.	Pharisaical Legalism: A righteousness of appearances without the heart\'92s transformation.\
\
Key Examples:\
	\'95	Simon Magus (Acts 8): Offering power without repentance.\
	\'95	The Beast of Revelation: Using authority and signs to mislead (Rev. 13).\
\
III. Theological Roots of False Light: Shadow, Not Substance\
\
The Nature of False Light:\
	\'95	Imitation: Mimics truth but lacks substance.\
	\'95	Temporary: Bright but fleeting, like a spark.\
	\'95	Self-Glorifying: Serves man or demonic ambition, not God\'92s glory.\
\
The True Light in Contrast:\
	\'95	John 1:9: \'93The true Light that gives light to everyone was coming into the world.\'94\
	\'95	Psalm 119:105: \'93Your Word is a lamp to my feet and a light to my path.\'94\
\
IV. The Prophetic Pattern of Fading Light\
\
The prophets repeatedly expose false light as a warning of coming judgment:\
	1.	The Golden Calf (Exodus 32):\
	\'95	Israel\'92s attempt to worship Yahweh through a false image.\
	2.	Jeremiah\'92s Lying Prophets (Jeremiah 23:16-17):\
	\'95	Prophets preaching peace without repentance.\
	3.	Baal Worship (1 Kings 18):\
	\'95	Elijah confronts false power with the fire of God.\
\
V. False Light and Personal Deception\
\
The Psychology of False Light:\
	\'95	Appears as Wisdom: Offers knowledge without accountability.\
	\'95	Focuses on Self: Elevates ego over truth.\
	\'95	Justifies Sin: Masks rebellion with half-truths.\
\
Key Verse:\
	\'95	Isaiah 5:20: \'93Woe to those who call evil good and good evil, who put darkness for light and light for darkness.\'94\
\
VI. Christ as the True Light That Exposes All Shadows\
\
