	\'95	Revelation 21:23: \'93The city has no need for the sun\'85 for the Lamb is its light.\'94\
\
How Christ Exposes False Light:\
	\'95	By Revealing the Father: Christ displays truthful revelation.\
	\'95	By Defeating the Accuser: Satan\'92s false accusations lose power at the Cross.\
	\'95	By Transforming the Heart: Christ restores vision to see the truth.\
\
VII. The False Light in the End Times: The Beast\'92s Mirage\
\
Revelation 13: The beast uses false signs to deceive the nations.\
	\'95	Miraculous Signs: Spectacle without substance.\
	\'95	Political Power: Earthly glory masking corruption.\
	\'95	Religious Blasphemy: False worship designed to mimic truth.\
\
The True Light Triumphs:\
	\'95	Revelation 22:5: \'93There will be no night there\'85 for the Lord God will give them light.\'94\
\
VIII. Practical Application: Walking in True Light\
	1.	Test the Light You Follow:\
	\'95	Is it centered on Christ?\
	\'95	Does it glorify God or self?\
	2.	Expose False Teaching:\
	\'95	Measure all truth by Scripture.\
	\'95	Reject man-centered wisdom masked as divine.\
	3.	Embrace the True Light:\
	\'95	Daily Scripture study as light for the path.\
	\'95	Christ-centered worship.\
\
IX. Summary Table: True vs. False Light\
\
Aspect	False Light	True Light\
Source	Self, Satan, Man	Christ, the Word of God\
Effect	Deception, Pride, Rebellion	Wisdom, Humility, Repentance\
Duration	Temporary, Fleeting	Eternal, Everlasting\
Goal	Control, Self-Glory	Communion, God\'92s Glory\
\
X. Final Call: Christ is the Only Unfading Light\
\
The false light of this world may appear enticing, but it fades because it is not rooted in the eternal truth of God.\
	\'95	Satan\'92s deceptions are merely shadows that dissolve before the face of Christ.\
	\'95	Christ is the Light of the world\'97the eternal flame that never fades.\
